<b>Subject:</b> Re: Help<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/pvp.cgi?read=1212" TARGET=_self>Help</A> (Ulwarth, The One)
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>>

<BR>It depends on WHO you are fighting. If I am a fighter type class going up against a magic based class I would use a 1h slashing weapon to disrupt his spells more often than with a 2h weapon. However with a fighter vs fighter I would go 2h to do big and hopefully fast damage. What I don't understand is why most magic based classes like wizards for example go to 2h blunt. Here is why I stay with peircing. So that I can disrupt the enemy spell casters spells more often. Some will say 2h does more damage and they are right SOMETIMES ( since magic based classes have low str the odds of them doing max damage with a staff is very low) they do more damage, BUT since when did wizards and necromancers ever depend on their melee damage to win the fight for them? So the occasional fact that you will hit for more damage against an opponent AND the fact that my dagger is worthless vs a fighter class(although so is that staff) doesn't break my beleif in peircing.
<P>Novandamis
<P>in a whole battle what is better, u use a long sword with the
<BR>&gt; protection of the shield or a halbard, or even a morning star or
<BR>&gt; a two-handed hammer????
<BR>
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
